title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup takes a Set<Class<?>> as input. The output is always "MySomeClass".
OB: The output of the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method should not always be "MySomeClass".
EB: classSet is not expected to always contain the class "MySomeClass".
SR: Modify the logic in the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method to correctly handle the input Set<Class<?>> and produce the expected output.
